import torch
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# ## 1 Configuration de base (auto-dtection du dossier data)
CANDIDATES = ["/workspace/data", "/data", "./data"]
ROOT_DATA = next((d for d in CANDIDATES if os.path.isdir(os.path.join(d, "NCT-CRC-HE-100K"))), None)
if ROOT_DATA is None:
    raise FileNotFoundError("Impossible de trouver le dossier de dataset (NCT-CRC-HE-100K). Vrifie le montage Docker.")
else:
    print(f" Dataset trouv dans : {ROOT_DATA}")

DEVICE = "cuda" if torch.cuda.is_available() else "cpu"
BATCH_SIZE = 8

print(f"Device utilis : {DEVICE}")

# ## 2 Chargement du dataset avec chantillonnage
MAX_PER_CLASS_TRAIN = 200
MAX_PER_CLASS_VAL = 50

print("\n Chargement du dataset TRAIN (chantillonn)...")
ds_train = HistoDataset(
    balance_per_class=True,
    root_data=ROOT_DATA,
    split="train",
    output_size=IMG_SIZE,
    thresholds_json_path="seuils_par_classe.json",
    vahadane_enable=True,
    vahadane_device=DEVICE,
    samples_per_class_per_epoch=MAX_PER_CLASS_TRAIN
)

print("\n Chargement du dataset VAL (chantillonn)...")
ds_val = HistoDataset(
    root_data=ROOT_DATA,
    split="val",
    output_size=IMG_SIZE,
    thresholds_json_path="seuils_par_classe.json",
    vahadane_enable=False,
    samples_per_class_per_epoch=MAX_PER_CLASS_VAL,
    no_repeat_eval=True
)

def subsample_dataset(ds, max_per_class=200):
    """Retourne un sous-ensemble quilibr sans dpasser max_per_class par classe.
    Version optimise : parcourt _epoch_indices une seule fois."""
    # Construire un dictionnaire classe -> liste d'indices en un seul passage
    by_class = {}
    for idx, (ci, _) in enumerate(ds._epoch_indices):
        if ci not in by_class:
            by_class[ci] = []
        by_class[ci].append(idx)
    
    # Slectionner max_per_class indices par classe
    selected_indices = []
    for ci in sorted(by_class.keys()):
        selected_indices.extend(by_class[ci][:max_per_class])
    
    return Subset(ds, selected_indices)


ds_train_small = subsample_dataset(ds_train, MAX_PER_CLASS_TRAIN)
ds_val_small = subsample_dataset(ds_val, MAX_PER_CLASS_VAL)

print(f"\nTaille finale train: {len(ds_train_small)}  |  val: {len(ds_val_small)}")

In[11]:
import time
import numpy as np
from tqdm import tqdm

def benchmark_dataloader(ds, batch_size=8, num_workers=0, n_batches=20, device=DEVICE):
    """Benchmark optimis du DataLoader avec mesure prcise des temps."""
    loader = DataLoader(ds, batch_size=batch_size, shuffle=True, num_workers=num_workers, 
                       pin_memory=(device.startswith("cuda")))
    
    # Pr-allocation pour viter les allocations dynamiques
    times = []
    start_global = time.time()

    # Warmup: premier batch pour initialiser les caches
    first_batch = next(iter(loader))
    _ = first_batch[0].to(device, non_blocking=True)
    if device.startswith("cuda"):
        torch.cuda.synchronize()
    
    # Reset timer aprs warmup
    start_global = time.time()
    
    for i, (x, y, path) in enumerate(tqdm(loader, total=n_batches, desc=" Lecture des batches")):
        t0 = time.time()
        x = x.to(device, non_blocking=True)
        # Synchronisation seulement si CUDA (vite l'appel inutile sur CPU)
        if device.startswith("cuda"):
            torch.cuda.synchronize()
        t_batch = time.time() - t0
        times.append(t_batch)
        if i + 1 >= n_batches:
            break

    total_time = time.time() - start_global
    mean_batch = np.mean(times)
    std_batch = np.std(times)
    imgs_per_sec = (batch_size * n_batches) / total_time

    print(f"\nTemps total: {total_time:.2f}s pour {n_batches} batches de {batch_size}")
    print(f" Temps moyen par batch: {mean_batch*1000:.1f}  {std_batch*1000:.1f} ms")
    print(f" Dbit moyen: {imgs_per_sec:.1f} images/s\n")

# Excution sur un sous-ensemble (pour viter la surcharge)
benchmark_dataloader(ds_train_small, batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, num_workers=0)

# Note: num_workers>0 dclenche une erreur qui est un bug d'interaction entre PyTorch multiprocessing
# et Jupyter/IPython (li  la gestion des sockets de communication entre workers)

# Vrification de l'quilibrage des classes
import torch
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from collections import Counter
from tqdm import tqdm

# --- Paramtres du test ---
N_BATCHES = 20  # nombre de batches  examiner
BATCH_SIZE = 8  # cohrent avec ton DataLoader
NUM_WORKERS = 0  # vite le multiprocessing sous Jupyter

loader = torch.utils.data.DataLoader(
    ds_train,
    batch_size=BATCH_SIZE,
    shuffle=True,
    num_workers=NUM_WORKERS
)

# --- Comptage des classes sur un chantillon ---
counts = Counter()
for i, (_, y, _) in enumerate(tqdm(loader, total=N_BATCHES, desc="Analyse des batches")):
    y = y.cpu().numpy()
    counts.update(y)
    if i >= N_BATCHES - 1:
        break

# --- Normalisation et affichage ---
labels = [ds_train.idx_to_class[i] for i in sorted(counts.keys())]
values = [counts[i] for i in sorted(counts.keys())]
total = sum(values)
proportions = np.array(values) / total * 100

# Rcupration des mappings depuis ton utilitaire
from p9dg.utils.class_mappings import make_idx_mappings

idx_to_name, idx_to_color, name_to_color = make_idx_mappings(ds_train.class_to_idx)

# Reconstruit un dictionnaire avec les cls du dataset ('ADI', 'BACK', etc.)
class_colors = {short: idx_to_color[idx] for idx, short in ds_train.idx_to_class.items()}


plt.figure(figsize=(8,4))
plt.bar(labels, proportions, color=[class_colors[c] for c in labels])
plt.title(f"Rpartition des classes dans {N_BATCHES} batches ({BATCH_SIZE*N_BATCHES} images)")
plt.ylabel("% d'images")
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# --- Rsum numrique ---
for cls, val in zip(labels, proportions):
    print(f"{cls:<6}  {val:5.1f}%")

#  3 Vrification visuelle de la normalisation Vahadane (multi-classes + moyenne couleur)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from PIL import Image
import numpy as np
import random

def avg_color(img: Image.Image):
    """Retourne la couleur moyenne RGB d'une image."""
    arr = np.asarray(img).astype(np.float32) / 255.0
    return arr.mean(axis=(0, 1))

# Slectionner 5 classes diffrentes alatoirement
selected_classes = random.sample(list(ds_train.paths_by_class.keys()), 5)

fig, axs = plt.subplots(len(selected_classes), 3, figsize=(12, 3 * len(selected_classes)))
fig.suptitle("Effet de la normalisation Vahadane sur 5 classes (avec couleur moyenne)", fontsize=14)

for row, ci in enumerate(selected_classes):
    class_name = ds_train.idx_to_class[ci]
    sample_path = random.choice(ds_train.paths_by_class[ci])
    
    img_raw = Image.open(sample_path)
    img_norm = ds_train.stain.normalize(img_raw)
    
    # Calcul des couleurs moyennes
    c_raw = avg_color(img_raw)
    c_norm = avg_color(img_norm)
    
    # --- Colonne 1 : image brute ---
    axs[row, 0].imshow(img_raw)
    axs[row, 0].set_title(f"{class_name}  Avant", fontsize=10)
    axs[row, 0].axis("off")
    
    # --- Colonne 2 : image normalise ---
    axs[row, 1].imshow(img_norm)
    axs[row, 1].set_title("Aprs normalisation", fontsize=10)
    axs[row, 1].axis("off")
    
    # --- Colonne 3 : couleur moyenne avant/aprs (patchs juxtaposs) ---
    patch = np.ones((50, 100, 3))
    patch[:, :50, :] = c_raw
    patch[:, 50:, :] = c_norm
    axs[row, 2].imshow(patch)
    axs[row, 2].set_title("Moyenne couleur\n(gauche=avant / droite=aprs)", fontsize=9)
    axs[row, 2].axis("off")

plt.tight_layout(rect=[0, 0, 1, 0.97])
plt.show()

# Teste combien d'images passent le filtre
import numpy as np
from PIL import Image
from tqdm import tqdm

results = {}
for ci, cname in ds_train.idx_to_class.items():
    thr = ds_train.class_thresholds.get(cname, {})
    ok_count, total = 0, len(ds_train.paths_by_class[ci])
    for path in np.random.choice(ds_train.paths_by_class[ci], min(50, total), replace=False):
        img = Image.open(path)
        if ds_train.qf.check(ds_train.qf.score(img), thr):
            ok_count += 1
    results[cname] = f"{ok_count}/{min(50, total)} OK"

print("\n Vrification du filtrage qualit (chantillon de 50 images max/classe) :")
for cname, res in results.items():
    print(f"{cname:<6}  {res}")

#  FORCER LE RECHARGEMENT DU MODULE ( excuter aprs modification du code source)
# Cette cellule supprime le module du cache Python et le recharge depuis le disque

import sys
import importlib

# Supprimer le module du cache s'il existe dj
modules_to_remove = [
    'p9dg.histo_dataset',
    'p9dg',
]

for mod_name in modules_to_remove:
    if mod_name in sys.modules:
        del sys.modules[mod_name]
        print(f"  Module {mod_name} supprim du cache")

# Recharger le module
from p9dg.histo_dataset import HistoDataset

# Vrifier que la nouvelle version est charge
import inspect
try:
    source = inspect.getsource(HistoDataset._build_epoch_indices)
    if '_used_indices_by_class' in source:
        print("\n Module recharg avec succs - version avec no_repeat_eval corrige")
    else:
        print("\n  Module recharg mais _used_indices_by_class non trouv")
except Exception as e:
    print(f"\n  Erreur lors de la vrification: {e}")

print("\n Vous pouvez maintenant utiliser HistoDataset avec no_repeat_eval=True")

#  TEST CRITIQUE 1: Vrification de no_repeat_eval=True en validation
# Ce test vrifie que les images ne se rptent pas entre les poques en mode validation
# C'est crucial pour garantir une valuation non biaise

print("=" * 70)
print("TEST CRITIQUE 1: no_repeat_eval=True en mode validation")
print("=" * 70)

# Crer un dataset de validation avec no_repeat_eval=True
ds_val_test = HistoDataset(
    root_data=ROOT_DATA,
    split="val",
    output_size=IMG_SIZE,
    thresholds_json_path="seuils_par_classe.json",
    vahadane_enable=False,
    samples_per_class_per_epoch=50,
    no_repeat_eval=True  #  Important : pas de rptition entre poques
)

print(f" Dataset de validation cr: {len(ds_val_test)} images")

# Collecter les chemins de l'poque 0
epoch_0_paths = set()
for i in range(len(ds_val_test)):
    _, _, path = ds_val_test[i]
    epoch_0_paths.add(os.path.basename(path))

print(f"poque 0: {len(epoch_0_paths)} images uniques")

# Passer  l'poque 1
ds_val_test.set_epoch(1)
epoch_1_paths = set()
for i in range(len(ds_val_test)):
    _, _, path = ds_val_test[i]
    epoch_1_paths.add(os.path.basename(path))

print(f"poque 1: {len(epoch_1_paths)} images uniques")

# Vrifier le chevauchement
overlap = epoch_0_paths & epoch_1_paths
overlap_count = len(overlap)

print(f" Chevauchement entre poques: {overlap_count} images")
print(f"   poque 0: {len(epoch_0_paths)} images")
print(f"   poque 1: {len(epoch_1_paths)} images")

if overlap_count == 0:
    print(" SUCCS: Aucune image rpte entre les poques (no_repeat_eval fonctionne)")
else:
    print(f" CHEC: {overlap_count} images se rptent entre les poques !")
    print(f"   Exemples de rptitions: {list(overlap)[:5]}")
    raise AssertionError("no_repeat_eval=True ne fonctionne pas correctement !")

#  TEST CRITIQUE 2: Cas limites du filtrage qualit
# Ce test vrifie le comportement quand le filtre rejette beaucoup d'images
# et s'assure que le mcanisme de retry fonctionne correctement

print("=" * 70)
print("TEST CRITIQUE 2: Cas limites du filtrage qualit")
print("=" * 70)

from PIL import Image
import numpy as np

# Analyser le taux de rejet par classe
print("\n Analyse du taux de rejet par classe (chantillon de 100 images/classe):")
print("-" * 70)

rejection_stats = {}
for ci, cname in ds_train.idx_to_class.items():
    paths = ds_train.paths_by_class[ci]
    sample_size = min(100, len(paths))
    sample_paths = np.random.choice(paths, size=sample_size, replace=False)
    
    rejected_count = 0
    ok_count = 0
    
    for path in sample_paths:
        try:
            img = Image.open(path)
            metrics = ds_train.qf.score(img)
            thr = ds_train.class_thresholds.get(cname, {})
            
            # Ajouter jpeg_blockiness si disponible (comme dans __getitem__)
            if cname in ds_train.block_stats:
                mu_s, sd_s = ds_train.block_stats[cname]["spatial"]
                mu_d, sd_d = ds_train.block_stats[cname]["dct"]
                sd_s = sd_s if (sd_s not in (0.0, None) and not np.isnan(sd_s)) else 1e-8
                sd_d = sd_d if (sd_d not in (0.0, None) and not np.isnan(sd_d)) else 1e-8
                z_s = (metrics["block_spatial"] - mu_s) / sd_s
                z_d = (metrics["block_dct"] - mu_d) / sd_d
                metrics["jpeg_blockiness"] = float((z_s + z_d) / 2.0)
            
            if ds_train.qf.check(metrics, thr):
                ok_count += 1
            else:
                rejected_count += 1
        except Exception as e:
            rejected_count += 1
    
    rejection_rate = rejected_count / sample_size
    rejection_stats[cname] = {
        'rejected': rejected_count,
        'ok': ok_count,
        'total': sample_size,
        'rate': rejection_rate
    }
    
    status = "" if rejection_rate > 0.7 else "" if rejection_rate < 0.3 else ""
    print(f"{status} {cname:<6}: {rejected_count:3d}/{sample_size:3d} rejet ({rejection_rate:5.1%})")

# Identifier les classes problmatiques
high_rejection = {k: v for k, v in rejection_stats.items() if v['rate'] > 0.7}
if high_rejection:
    print("\n  Classes avec taux de rejet > 70%:")
    for cname, stats in high_rejection.items():
        print(f"   - {cname}: {stats['rate']:.1%} rejet ({stats['rejected']}/{stats['total']})")

# Test du mcanisme de retry dans __getitem__
print("\n" + "-" * 70)
print("Test du mcanisme de retry (max 5 tentatives) dans __getitem__:")
print("-" * 70)

# Tester que __getitem__ fonctionne mme pour les classes avec fort taux de rejet
retry_success = True
retry_errors = []

for cname in list(high_rejection.keys())[:3]:  # Tester les 3 premires classes problmatiques
    ci = None
    for idx, name in ds_train.idx_to_class.items():
        if name == cname:
            ci = idx
            break
    
    if ci is None:
        continue
    
    print(f"\n Test de rcupration pour {cname} (taux de rejet: {rejection_stats[cname]['rate']:.1%}):")
    
    # Essayer de rcuprer plusieurs chantillons
    success_count = 0
    for attempt in range(10):
        try:
            # Trouver un index qui correspond  cette classe
            class_indices = [i for i, (c, _) in enumerate(ds_train._epoch_indices) if c == ci]
            if not class_indices:
                break
            
            idx = class_indices[attempt % len(class_indices)]
            x, y, path = ds_train[idx]
            
            # Vrifier que l'image est valide
            assert x.shape == (3, IMG_SIZE, IMG_SIZE), f"Shape incorrecte: {x.shape}"
            assert y == ci, f"Classe incorrecte: {y} != {ci}"
            success_count += 1
        except Exception as e:
            retry_errors.append(f"{cname} (tentative {attempt}): {str(e)}")
    
    print(f"    {success_count}/10 chantillons rcuprs avec succs")
    
    if success_count < 5:
        print(f"     Attention: Seulement {success_count}/10 russites pour {cname}")
        retry_success = False

if retry_success:
    print("\n SUCCS: Le mcanisme de retry fonctionne correctement")
else:
    print("\n  ATTENTION: Certaines classes ont des difficults  fournir des chantillons valides")
    if retry_errors:
        print("   Erreurs rencontres:")
        for err in retry_errors[:5]:
            print(f"   - {err}")

# Vrification finale
print("\n" + "-" * 70)
print("Rsum:")
print("-" * 70)
total_rejected = sum(s['rejected'] for s in rejection_stats.values())
total_tested = sum(s['total'] for s in rejection_stats.values())
overall_rate = total_rejected / total_tested

print(f"Taux de rejet global: {overall_rate:.1%} ({total_rejected}/{total_tested})")
print(f"Classes avec rejet > 70%: {len(high_rejection)}/{len(rejection_stats)}")

if overall_rate > 0.5:
    print("\n  ATTENTION: Taux de rejet global > 50% - le dataset pourrait tre trop petit")
elif len(high_rejection) > 0:
    print(f"\n  ATTENTION: {len(high_rejection)} classe(s) avec rejet > 70%")
else:
    print("\n Taux de rejet acceptable pour toutes les classes")

print("\n" + "=" * 70)

from collections import Counter

def epoch_class_counts(ds):
    c = Counter(ci for (ci, _) in ds._epoch_indices)
    return {ds.idx_to_class[k]: v for k, v in c.items()}

epoch_class_counts(ds_gan)
